snippet: The National League for Democracy, led by the Nobel peace laureate Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, won 390 seats, compared with 42 seats for the governing party.
abstract: Final vote count in Myanmar election shows overwhelming victory for opposition party National League for Democracy, led by Daw Aung San Suu Kyi;  timing of transition to new government still unclear.
lead_paragraph: The National League for Democracy, led by the Nobel peace laureate Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, won 390 seats, compared with 42 seats for the governing party.

headline.main: Final Vote Tally Confirms Rout by Myanmar Opposition
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Asia; Myanmar: Official Tally Is Announced
